</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_structure_arm  Entity: Building  
   <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Building">
A <b>Building</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> that defines a version of a construction works, that has the provision of shelter for its 
occupants or contents as one of its main purposes and is usually enclosed and designed to stand permanently in one place.
<p>A <b>Building</b> shall be owned by one <express_ref linkend="person_organization:arm:Person_organization_arm.Person_in_organization"/> or one <express_ref linkend="person_organization:arm:Person_organization_arm.Organization"/>.</p>
		<p>A <b>Building</b> shall contain at least a building section.</p>
		<note>Information about life-cycle phase addressed by the definition of the building can be provided within the inherited attributes <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition.initial_context"/> and <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition.additional_contexts"/>.</note>
	</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Building.wr:WR1">
A <b>Building</b> shall be referred to by a <express_ref linkend="person_organization_assignment:arm:Person_organization_assignment_arm.Organization_or_person_in_organization_assignment"/> that has role 'owner'.
</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Building.wr:WR2">
A <b>Building</b> shall be associated with at least a <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building_section"/> through instances of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship"/>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_structure_arm  Entity: Building_level  
   <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building_level"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Building_level">
A <b>Building_level</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/>. It is part of a <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building"/> that consists of one or more areas accessible through primarily
horizontal access paths. 
<p>A <b>Building_level</b> may be a <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Sublevel"/> or may have <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Sublevel"/> instances.
</p>
		<example> Buildings are often structured into building levels. Building items such as spaces, walls, building services equipment are frequently assigned to building levels. 
Other building items such as chimneys and elevator compartments may cut accross building levels and may not be assigned to building levels.</example>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_structure_arm  Entity: Building_level_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building_level_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Building_level_assignment"> 
A <b>Building_level_assignment</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship"/>. It is the assignment of a <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building_level"/> 
	 to <express_ref linkend="building_item:arm:Building_item_arm.Building_item"/> instances.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_structure_arm  Entity: Building_level_assignment  Attribute: relating_view RENAMED assigned_level 
   <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building_level_assignment.relating_view RENAMED assigned_level"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Building_level_assignment.assigned_level"> the <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building_level"/> that is assigned with a 
<express_ref linkend="building_item:arm:Building_item_arm.Building_item"/>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_structure_arm  Entity: Building_level_assignment  Attribute: related_view RENAMED assigned_item 
   <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building_level_assignment.related_view RENAMED assigned_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Building_level_assignment.assigned_item"> the 
<express_ref linkend="building_item:arm:Building_item_arm.Building_item"/> to which the <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building_level"/> is assigned.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_structure_arm  Entity: Building_section  
   <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building_section"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Building_section">
A <b>Building_section</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> that identifies a logical section in a Building.
<note>Logical segments of a building are defined based on local coordinate systems for functional or definitional convenience.
</note>
		<example>Buildings are commonly broken down, during design, in individual structures that are integrated at a later point in time.
Wings of an hospital, a library or an office complex are examples of building sections.
</example>
	</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Building_section.wr:WR1">
A <b>Building_section</b> shall be the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.related_view"/> of exactly one <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship"/> whose <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.relating_view"/> identifies the <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building"/> that contains the considered <b>Building_section</b>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_structure_arm  Entity: Item_assembly  
   <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Item_assembly"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Item_assembly">
An <b>Item_assembly</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> that defines a view of an assembly of 
<express_ref linkend="building_item:arm:Building_item_arm.Building_item"/> instances or <b>Item_assembly</b> instances.
The components are combined to form a more complex or larger object.
<example>Trusses and frames are typical element assemblies for structural elements. A pipeline
is a typical example of an element assembly for building services equipment.</example>
		<p>As subtype of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/>, an <b>Item_assembly</b> defines a view of a version of a Product.
Where applicable, the category of that product shall be taken among the categories:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>roof: The covering or upper part of a building that has a primary function of protecting the
building from weather;</li>
			<li>stairway: One or more flights of stairs used to pass from one floor of a building to another;
<note>The flights of stairs are often separated by landings and the stairway includes the supporting structure.
</note>
			</li>
			<li>vertical passage enclosure: The structure that surrounds, frames, or encloses a vertical
opening through the floors of a building.</li>
		</ul>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_structure_arm  Entity: Item_assembly  Attribute: components 
   <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Item_assembly.components"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Item_assembly.component_relationships">
the set of instances of <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Assembly_component_relationship"/> in which the <b>Item_assembly</b> plays the role of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.relating_view"/> and 
that identify the components of the <b>Item_assembly</b>.
</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Item_assembly.wr:WR1">
component_relationships shall only contain elements whose type is one of the types listed in <b>assembly_item</b> type.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_structure_arm  Entity: Item_proximity_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Item_proximity_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Item_proximity_relationship">
An <b>Item_proximity_relationship</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship"/> that defines an association between a 
<express_ref linkend="building_item:arm:Building_item_arm.Building_item"/> and another 
<express_ref linkend="building_item:arm:Building_item_arm.Building_item"/> that is near it.
<p>Where applicable, the inherited <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.relation_type"/>  attribute shall take one of the following values:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>'space to element': the item in proximity bounds the space;
</li>
			<li>'penetration': the item in proximity penetrates or "goes through" the
item;</li>
			<li>'touch': the item in proximity is in contact with the item.</li>
		</ul>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_structure_arm  Entity: Item_proximity_relationship  Attribute: relating_view RENAMED item_in_proximity 
   <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Item_proximity_relationship.relating_view RENAMED item_in_proximity"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Item_proximity_relationship.relating_view RENAMED item_in_proximity"> the specification of the 
<express_ref linkend="building_item:arm:Building_item_arm.Building_item"/> that are near another
<express_ref linkend="building_item:arm:Building_item_arm.Building_item"/>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_structure_arm  Entity: Item_proximity_relationship  Attribute: related_view RENAMED item 
   <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Item_proximity_relationship.related_view RENAMED item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Item_proximity_relationship.related_view RENAMED item"> the specification of the 
<express_ref linkend="building_item:arm:Building_item_arm.Building_item"/> near which another 
<express_ref linkend="building_item:arm:Building_item_arm.Building_item"/> is
positioned.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_structure_arm  Entity: Item_proximity_relationship  Attribute: relation_type RENAMED relationship_type 
   <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Item_proximity_relationship.relation_type RENAMED relationship_type"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Item_proximity_relationship.relation_type RENAMED relationship_type">a descriptive label of proximity. The value is either user defined or
predefined.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_structure_arm  Entity: Sublevel  
   <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Sublevel"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Sublevel">A <b>Sublevel</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building_level"/> that is a constituent of another <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building_level"/>.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Building_structure_arm  Entity: Sublevel  Attribute: belongs_to 
   <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Sublevel.belongs_to"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Building_structure_arm.Sublevel.belongs_to"> the specification of the <express_ref linkend="building_structure:arm:Building_structure_arm.Building_level"/> of which the <b>Sublevel</b> is a part.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
